---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const updated = "2026-06-19";
---

<BaseLayout
	title="Privacy policy"
	description="What Journal collects, what it doesn't, and your rights."
>
	<header class="container-prose page-head">
		<p class="eyebrow"><a href="/">Journal</a> / <a href="/legal/">Legal</a> / Privacy</p>
		<h1>Privacy policy</h1>
		<p class="meta">Last updated: {updated}</p>
	</header>

	<article class="container-prose prose">
		<h2>Who runs this</h2>
		<p>
			journal.oriz.in is part of the <a href="https://oriz.in">oriz family</a>, operated by
			Chirag Singhal, based in Bhubaneswar, Odisha, India. Contact:
			<a href="mailto:whyiswhen@gmail.com">whyiswhen@gmail.com</a>.
		</p>

		<h2>What we collect</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>
				<strong>Cloudflare Web Analytics</strong> — aggregate page views and country.
				Cookieless. No personal identifiers.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Authentication</strong> — if you sign in, Firebase Authentication stores
				your email, display name, and profile photo (if you sign in with Google/GitHub).
				We never see your password. You can also sign in anonymously.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Journal entries + settings</strong> — your entries, tags, templates,
				goals, and preferences are stored in Firestore under your user ID. They are
				readable and writable only by you, enforced by Firestore security rules. Nobody
				else, including the operator, can read them.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Contact form</strong> — submissions go through Web3Forms which
				forwards them to my email. Web3Forms keeps copies; see their privacy policy.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Display ads</strong> — once approved, Google AdSense may set
				cookies to personalize ads. You can opt out via the consent banner or
				at <a href="https://adssettings.google.com">adssettings.google.com</a>.
			</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>What we don't do</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>No tracking across sessions for analytics (Cloudflare is anonymous).</li>
			<li>No selling of personal data to third parties.</li>
			<li>No reading of your journal entries — they live encrypted-in-transit in Firestore under your <code>uid</code>.</li>
			<li>No newsletters unless you explicitly subscribe.</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>Your rights</h2>
		<p>
			You can delete your account from the in-app settings, which wipes every
			Firestore document owned by your <code>uid</code> — entries, templates,
			tags, goals, settings, counters. Export everything first via Settings →
			Export if you want a copy.
		</p>
		<p>
			Under India's DPDP Act 2023, you have the right to access, correct,
			and delete your personal data. Contact the
			<a href="/legal/grievance/">grievance officer</a>.
		</p>

		<h2>Children</h2>
		<p>
			Journal is not directed at children under 13. If you believe a child has
			provided data to us, contact the grievance officer for removal.
		</p>

		<h2>Changes</h2>
		<p>
			We will update this page when the practice changes, with the new date
			at the top. Material changes get a banner on the site.
		</p>
	</article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
	.page-head {
		padding-block: 3rem 1.5rem;
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule, #d9d0bd);
	}
	.eyebrow {
		color: var(--color-ink-muted, #6b6256);
		font-size: 0.8125rem;
		margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
	}
	.eyebrow a { color: var(--color-ink-muted, #6b6256); text-decoration: none; }
	h1 {
		font-family: var(--font-display, "Fraunces", serif);
		font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.75rem);
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
		margin: 0;
	}
	.meta { color: var(--color-ink-subtle, #9a9082); font-size: 0.875rem; margin: 0.5rem 0 0; }
	.prose {
		padding-block: 2.5rem 4rem;
		line-height: 1.7;
		font-size: 1.0625rem;
	}
	.prose h2 {
		font-family: var(--font-display, "Fraunces", serif);
		font-size: 1.375rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
	}
	.prose ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; margin: 0 0 1.25rem; }
	.prose li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
	.prose p { margin: 0 0 1.25rem; }
	.prose a { color: var(--color-sienna, #b45309); }
	.prose code {
		background: var(--color-paper-soft, #f1ece2);
		padding: 0.125em 0.375em;
		border-radius: 0.25rem;
		font-size: 0.875em;
	}
	.container-prose {
		max-width: 720px;
		margin-inline: auto;
		padding-inline: clamp(1rem, 4vw, 2rem);
	}
</style>
